<section xml:id="sec-boolean-algebra" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>Boolean Algebra</title><idx><h>Boolean Algebra</h></idx>
    <p>
        A <term>Boolean algebra</term> is a bounded lattice that is both complemented and distributive.
    </p>
    <p>
         Let's define the <c>is_boolean_algebra()</c> function to determine whether a given poset is a Boolean algebra. The function accepts a finite partially ordered set as input and returns a tuple containing a boolean value and a message explaining the result. Run the following cell to define the function and call it in other cells.
    </p>
    <sage>
        <input>
            def is_boolean_algebra(P):
                try:
                    L = LatticePoset(P)
                except ValueError as e:
                    return False, str(e)
                if not L.is_bounded():
                    return False, "The lattice is not bounded."
                if not L.is_distributive():
                    return False, "The lattice is not distributive."
                if not L.is_complemented():
                    return False, "The lattice is not complemented."
                return True, "The poset is a Boolean algebra."

            print("Ready to call `is_boolean_algebra`")
        </input>
    </sage>
    <p>
        Let's check if the the divisor lattice of <m>30</m> is a Boolean algebra.
    </p>
    <sage>
        <input>
            dl_30 = Posets.DivisorLattice(30)
            show(dl_30)

            is_boolean_algebra(dl_30)
        </input>
    </sage>
    <p>
        Now for the divisor lattice of <m>20</m>:
    </p>
    <sage>
        <input>
            dl_20 = Posets.DivisorLattice(20)
            show(dl_20)

            is_boolean_algebra(dl_20)
        </input>
    </sage>
    <p>
        Let's check if the poset, <m>P</m> is a Boolean algebra.
    </p>
    <sage>
        <input>
            P = Poset(({0,1,2,3,4}, [(0,1),(0,3),(1,2),(3,4)]))
            show(P)

            is_boolean_algebra(P)
        </input>
    </sage>
    <p>
        Let's check if the following diamond poset is a Boolean algebra.
    </p>
    <sage>
        <input>
            D = posets.DiamondPoset(5)
            show(D)

            is_boolean_algebra(D)
        </input>
    </sage>
    <p>
        Here is a classic lattice in the field of computer science:
    </p>
    <sage>
        <input>
            B = posets.BooleanLattice(1)
            show(B)

            is_boolean_algebra(B)
        </input>
    </sage>
